.SH NAME
octane-keywords-resolve - Resolve a step text to a keyword pattern


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBoctane keywords resolve  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
resolve matches  against registered keywords
and prints the matched pattern and extracted arguments.

.PP
If no keyword matches, the command prints a "no match" message with
the closest suggestion (if any) and exits 0.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for resolve


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--cache-dir\fP=""
	override the cache directory (default: $XDG_CACHE_HOME/octane/cache)

.PP
\fB--config\fP="octane.yml"
	path to octane.yml configuration file

.PP
\fB--no-cache\fP[=false]
	bypass the result cache entirely

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=false]
	enable verbose output


